cp — copy files and directory trees

SYNOPSIS
  cp [-r] SRC... DST

DESCRIPTION
  Copies each SRC to DST. If DST is a directory, every SRC is copied
  inside it; otherwise exactly one SRC is required and its content is
  copied to DST.

  -r enables directory recursion. Without it, copying a directory is
  a hard error.

  Copies always read-then-write; OC's filesystem component has no clone
  primitive. Cross-mount copies work the same as same-mount copies — the
  payload simply transits through Lua memory.

EXAMPLES
  cp data.txt /backup/
  cp -r /home/alex /mnt/external/alex

SEE ALSO
  mv(1), rm(1), ls(1)
